### Use this procedure to Disable a single User in Umbraco

> This is the Json-rpc call to disable a user from umbraco. 

**PAYLOAD:**

 * method (string) `[required]` : "DisableUser"
 * id (int) `[required]` *a number generated by the api call origin*
 * params (object) `[required]` *the actual body of the call*
    - authorization `[required]` *this is the total code api information to authenticate with umbraco to process requests*
        + AppId (Guid) `[required]`     
        + ApiKey (Guid) `[required]`
	- payload: `[required]`
    	+ Username (string) `[required]` *the user to be disabled, usually the main user; example => "bobdylan@outlook.com"*

#### Since the procedure is Json-Rpc, it must be wrapped with Json-Rpc objects

		{
			"method": <<Method Name>>,
			"params": <<parameters for the request>>,
			"id": <<id of the request>>
		}
		
#### Example 		
		
		{
		    "method": "DisableUser",
		    "params": {
		        "authorization": {
		            "AppId": "4d53bce03ec34c0a911182d4c228ee6c",
		            "ApiKey": "zYPSLb7uYA1NHFHtvZw+DGyqJr2P2/sT8puaAP+NFgs="
		        },
		        "tenant": {
		            "Username": "bobdylan@outlook.com"
		        }
		    },
		    "id": 6
		}
		
### Returns confirmation the user has been disabled

#### Example Response

		{
		    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
		    "result": {
		        "Message": "User disabled",
		        "TenantUid": null,
		        "Status": "Ok",
		        "Data": {
		            "Username": "bobdylan2@outlook.com"
		        }
		    },
		    "id": 6
		}
		
## Possible Errors

		Unhandled = -999,
        TenantNotFound = 504,
        UsernameAlreadyDisabled = 703,
        UsernameDoesNotExist = 705,

### Use this procedure to Change a User's Password in Umbraco

> This is the Json-rpc call to change the password for a specific umbraco user. 

**PAYLOAD:**

 - method (string) `[required]` : "ChangePassword"
 - id (int) `[required]` *a number generated by the api call origin*
 - params (object) `[required]` *the actual body of the call*
 	+ authorization *this is the total code api information to authenticate with umbraco to process requests*
		* AppId (Guid) `[required]`     
		* ApiKey (Guid) `[required]`
 	+ payload `[required]`
		* password (string) `[required]` *must comply with requirements; example => 'Password!1234'*
		* username (string) `[required]` *umbraco uses email address as username; example => myemail@email.com*

#### Since the procedure is Json-Rpc, it must be wrapped with Json-Rpc objects

		{
			"method": <<Method Name>>,
			"params": <<parameters for the request>>,
			"id": <<id of the request>>
		}
		
		
#### Example

		{
		    "method": "ChangePassword",
		    "params": {
		        "authorization": {
		            "AppId": "4d53bce03ec34c0a911182d4c228ee6c",
		            "ApiKey": "zYPSLb7uYA1NHFHtvZw+DGyqJr2P2/sT8puaAP+NFgs="
		        },
		        "payload": {
		            "Password": "Password1234!",
		            "Username": "janedoe@outlook.com"
		        }
		    },
		    "id": 9
		}
		
### Returns Confirmation the password has been changed

#### Example Response

		{
		    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
		    "result": {
		        "Message": "Password for janedoe@outlook.com changed",
		        "TenantUid": null,
		        "Status": "Ok",
		        "Data": {
		            "Username": "janedoe@outlook.com",
		            "Password": "Password1234!"
		        }
		    },
		    "id": 9
		}
		
## Possible Errors

		Unhandled = -999,
        UsernameDoesNotExist = 705,

